    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Curacao</placeName>
                <date>23rd Oct. 1850</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Isc. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I recd. Your form<lb/> of <date>4th</date> Ult with the Occt. I was
                glad to see the Citrons &amp; Palms<lb/> had arrived at <placeName>New
                    York</placeName>. I hope they also arrived safely with you &amp;<lb/> proved
                satisfactory. I presume what you say about the reforms<lb/> of your prayer Books in
                any way you may Conclude to Act please<lb/> always consider me your friend, and I
                shall be happy to serve you<lb/> I shall keep in mind in <date>March</date> next to
                return you all the<lb/> prayer Books I may have of yours unsold, these
                    <sic>hollidays</sic> I have<lb/> only sold one sett for $25.—I therefore enclose
                you my dft on<lb/>
                <persName>Mess Joseph Foulke</persName>
                <del>and</del> &amp; son for $40., which is more than the Books<lb/> but I have recd
                from <persName>Mr Decasseres</persName> 48 for you to pass for the<lb/>
                    Boo<add>?</add> of the <placeName>Holy land</placeName> which you will oblige me
                by acknowledging<lb/> in some public paper or your Occident the Remainder will
                stand<lb/> to my credit till I send you your a<lb/>current.</p>
            <p>I regret much to presume you have lost the post of Hasan I hope<lb/> your enemies may
                soon see their error, and reinstate <add>you</add>, and at<lb/> any rate I hope the
                Lord will bless what ever you may undertake</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>the Tephillim, &amp;c are still in hands if you wish them returned<lb/> please let me
                know the people here find them too high price—<lb/> I don't fully<add>?</add>
                understand that part of your letter relative to my<lb/> cousin <persName>Mr Jm
                    Daunt</persName> please remember me to him and his good lady<lb/> please tell
                the latter as there is no communication between one <del>
                    <add>?</add>
                </del><lb/> party I have had little or no chance of being of service to her<lb/> but
                should an opportunity offer she may Calculate on me</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I am Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Your Ob. Ser. &amp; friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">M Daunt</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <del>Care of <persName>Mrss Gaff<add>?</add></persName>
                </del>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <del><persName>Foulke</persName> &amp; S<add>?</add></del>
            </p>
